Leonard Henry Courtney, 1st Baron Courtney of Penwith, PC (6 July 1832 â€“ 11 May 1918) was a British politician, academic and man of letters. He was a member of William Ewart Gladstone's second administration from 1880 to 1883 and served as Chairman of Ways and Means (Deputy Speaker of the House of Commons) between 1886 and 1893.
